parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling when Pulling in the Clutch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling when pulling in the clutch can cause the motorcycle to suddenly come to a stop, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially when riding in heavy traffic or at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine RPMs drop below 1000 RPM
the engine stalls or dies when pulling in the clutch
the motorcycle comes to a sudden stop
the engine stalls repeatedly when pulling in the clutch
the engine stalls more frequently when the motorcycle has been sitting in the sun for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling when Clutch is Disengaged
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling when the clutch is disengaged can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially for new or inexperienced riders.
symptoms: The engine stalls when the clutch is disengaged
often when coming to a stop or slowing down; the bike may come to an instant stop
causing loss of control or accidents; the idle speed may drop significantly before recovering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the rider stranded, especially when it occurs at critical times such as when approaching a stop sign or navigating a curve.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down without warning
the vehicle loses power or momentum
the rider experiences a loss of control.
